### Prompt: Implement Complete PDF Tools Suite for phung.work
### Objective
Build a professional, browser-first PDF Tools module for phung.work, comparable to iLovePDF, SmallPDF, PDF24, Sejda, TinyWow and other modern online PDF platforms.
The implementation must follow the existing architecture, design system, routing, and reusable components already used by phung.work.
### Core Principles
* Everything runs locally in the browser whenever technically possible.
* No backend dependency for standard PDF processing.
* User files never leave the browser unless explicitly required.
* Fast, responsive, and memory-efficient.
* Mobile responsive.
* Desktop optimized.
* Dark mode compatible.
* Accessible (WCAG AA).
* Modular architecture.
* Code splitting and lazy loading.
* Reusable components and hooks.
* Do not modify existing application flow or routing unless absolutely necessary.
### Shared Features
Every PDF tool must include:
* Hero title
* Description
* Supported formats
* Drag & Drop upload
* Multi-file upload
